title: Choosing Our Enemies
new-page: true
view-if: (year <= 1932 and enemies_timer <= 0) or (sandbox = 1 and enemies_timer <= 0)
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; enemies_timer = 12 + austerity_fortimers if sandbox = 0; enemies_timer = 10 + austerity_fortimers if sandbox = 1; enemy_1 = 0; enemy_2 = 0; enemy_3 = 0
is-card: true
card-image: img/poster_1.png
tags: party_affairs

= Choosing Our Enemies

The Vorwärts machine must be aimed at something. Our media, our campaigners, our speakers on street corners — they all need a face to argue against. Choosing our enemies carefully shapes how workers, the unemployed, and the middle classes see us.

We may designate up to three targets. Our primary enemy will bear the full weight of our rhetoric; the second and third will receive a lighter but still meaningful share of our attention.

Who stands against us first?

- @primary_kpd: The KPD — the Communists.
- @primary_nsdap: The NSDAP — the Nazis.
- @primary_dnvp: The DNVP — the Nationalists.
- @primary_z: The Zentrum Party.
- @primary_dvp: The DVP — the People's Party.
- @primary_bvp: The BVP — the Bavarian conservatives.
- @primary_wp: The WP — the Economic Party.
- @primary_ddp: The DDP — the Democrats.
- @primary_sapd: The SAPD — the Socialist splinter.
- @primary_csvd: The CSVD — the Christian Socials.
- @primary_cnbl: The CNBL — the agrarian nationalists.
- @easy_discard

@primary_kpd
view-if: (kpd_votes > 0 or kpd_r > 0) and ideology != "left"
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "KPD"; reformist_strength += 5; left_dissent += 8; reformist_dissent -= 5; kpd_relation -= 10; dvp_relation += 5; z_relation += 5; workers_kpd -= 4 if workers_kpd < 25; wp_relation += 4; bvp_relation += 5; dnvp_relation += 3 if dnvp_line = 1 or not dnvp_line
go-to: secondary

Targeting the Communists wins approval from the reformist wing and quiet nods from our bourgeois partners. The left of our party is furious, and any future reconciliation with the KPD will be harder. The street-level rivalry with Communist organizers will also intensify.

@primary_nsdap
view-if: nsdap_votes > 0 or nsdap_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "NSDAP"; neorevisionist_strength += 5; nazi_urgency += 1 if nazi_urgency > 0; workers_nsdap -= 4 if nazi_urgency > 0; workers_spd -= 1 if nazi_urgency <= 0; nsdap_relation -= 6
go-to: secondary

[? if nazi_urgency == 0 or nsdap_r < 10: The NSDAP is still a fringe outfit. Some in the party question whether we are wasting our breath on them. ?]
[? if nazi_urgency > 0 and nsdap_r >= 10: The Nazis are growing fast. Making them our primary target sends a clear signal to every worker still wavering. ?]

@primary_dnvp
view-if: dnvp_votes > 0 or dnvp_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "DNVP"; workers_dnvp *= 0.87; old_middle_dnvp *= 0.95; new_middle_dnvp *= 0.91; rural_dnvp *= 0.96; dnvp_relation -= 8; dnvp_relation -= 5 if dnvp_line = 1; bvp_relation -= 3
go-to: secondary

The Nationalists and monarchists make a natural enemy. Our anti-Junker rhetoric plays well in the industrial cities, though rural voters who still back the DNVP are harder to peel away.

@primary_z
view-if: z_votes > 0 or z_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "Z"; z_relation -= 7; workers_z *= 0.93; unemployed_z *= 0.88; catholics_z *= 0.97; left_dissent -= 3; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_weimar_coalition
go-to: secondary

Attacking the Zentrum strains any governing arrangement we have with them, and Catholic workers will not easily forgive us. The left finds it satisfying regardless.

@primary_dvp
view-if: dvp_votes > 0 or dvp_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "DVP"; left_strength += 3; dvp_relation -= 8; z_relation -= 2; ddp_relation -= 3; old_middle_spd -= 2; coalition_dissent += 1; workers_dvp -= 4; new_middle_dvp -= 2; reformist_dissent += 4; kpd_relation += 1
go-to: secondary

The industrial interests behind the DVP make them an easy target for class-conscious rhetoric. The reformist wing worries about burning bridges with moderate liberals.

@primary_bvp
view-if: bvp_votes > 0 or bvp_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "BVP"; bvp_relation -= 6; z_relation -= 4; old_middle_bvp *= 0.98; workers_bvp *= 0.93; rural_bvp *= 0.97; new_middle_bvp *= 0.93; unemployed_bvp *= 0.78
go-to: secondary

The Bavarian conservatives are a regional target, but attacking them strains our already difficult relationship with the Zentrum as well. The effect in Prussia and the north will be limited.

@primary_wp
view-if: wp_votes > 0 or wp_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "WP"; wp_relation -= 7; dvp_relation -= 3 if dvp_relation < 40; old_middle_wp *= 0.98; new_middle_wp *= 0.98; workers_wp *= 0.96; unemployed_wp *= 0.93; rural_wp *= 0.97; catholics_wp *= 0.96; inflation *= 0.99
go-to: secondary

The Economic Party presents itself as a middle-class defender while sitting close to industrialist interests. We can expose that contradiction, though it costs us with the petty bourgeoisie.

@primary_ddp
view-if: ddp_votes > 0 or ddp_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "DDP"; ddp_relation -= 9; dvp_relation -= 2 if dvp_relation < 40; old_middle_ddp *= 0.98; new_middle_ddp *= 0.97; workers_ddp *= 0.94; unemployed_ddp *= 0.93; rural_ddp *= 0.97; catholics_ddp *= 0.97; reformist_dissent += 5; left_dissent -= 3; coalition_dissent += 1 if in_weimar_coalition
go-to: secondary

The Democrats once stood for Weimar. Going after them now alienates our liberal allies and the reformist wing. The left approves.

@primary_sapd
view-if: sapd_votes > 0 or sapd_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "SAPD"; left_dissent += 10; reformist_dissent -= 3; sapd_relation -= 8; workers_sapd -= 3; kpd_relation -= 3
go-to: secondary

Attacking the SAPD splinter as adventurist and irresponsible may win back some reformist workers, but it deepens the fracture on the left and looks petty if they remain small.

@primary_csvd
view-if: csvd_votes > 0 or csvd_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "CSVD"; csvd_relation -= 6; catholics_csvd *= 0.97; workers_csvd *= 0.95; z_relation -= 2; reformist_dissent += 2
go-to: secondary

The Christian Social movement is a niche target, but one that may peel some religious workers away from confessional politics — at the cost of further straining Catholic relations.

@primary_cnbl
view-if: cnbl_votes > 0 or cnbl_r > 0
on-arrival: enemy_1 = "CNBL"; cnbl_relation -= 6; rural_cnbl *= 0.97; old_middle_cnbl *= 0.98; dnvp_relation -= 2; workers_spd += 1
go-to: secondary

The agrarian nationalists are not our natural constituency in any case, but making them a visible enemy signals to rural labourers that we are paying attention to the land question.

@secondary

= Our second target

We have turned our sights on the [+ enemy_1 +]. Now, who draws our secondary fire — a softer but still pointed criticism?

- @secondary_kpd: The KPD.
- @secondary_nsdap: The NSDAP.
- @secondary_dnvp: The DNVP.
- @secondary_z: The Zentrum Party.
- @secondary_dvp: The DVP.
- @secondary_bvp: The BVP.
- @secondary_wp: The WP.
- @secondary_ddp: The DDP.
- @secondary_sapd: The SAPD.
- @secondary_csvd: The CSVD.
- @secondary_cnbl: The CNBL.
- @skip_secondary: We focus on one enemy for now.

@secondary_kpd
view-if: (kpd_votes > 0 or kpd_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "KPD" and ideology != "left"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "KPD"; kpd_relation -= 5; workers_kpd -= 2 if workers_kpd < 25; dvp_relation += 2; reformist_dissent -= 3; left_dissent += 4
go-to: tertiary

Secondary criticism of the Communists reinforces our anti-extremist credentials without making them our sole focus.

@secondary_nsdap
view-if: (nsdap_votes > 0 or nsdap_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "NSDAP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "NSDAP"; nsdap_relation -= 3; workers_nsdap -= 2 if nazi_urgency > 0; neorevisionist_strength += 2
go-to: tertiary

We keep the Nazis in our sights as a secondary target — enough to remind voters of the threat without making it our sole campaign.

@secondary_dnvp
view-if: (dnvp_votes > 0 or dnvp_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "DNVP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "DNVP"; dnvp_relation -= 4; workers_dnvp *= 0.95; dnvp_relation -= 3 if dnvp_line = 1
go-to: tertiary

We keep up a steady drumbeat against Nationalist reaction as a secondary theme.

@secondary_z
view-if: (z_votes > 0 or z_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "Z"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "Z"; z_relation -= 3; workers_z *= 0.97; catholics_z *= 0.99; coalition_dissent += 0.5 if in_weimar_coalition
go-to: tertiary

Secondary criticism of the Zentrum is pointed but restrained — enough to draw a contrast, not enough to fully rupture relations.

@secondary_dvp
view-if: (dvp_votes > 0 or dvp_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "DVP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "DVP"; dvp_relation -= 4; workers_dvp -= 2; reformist_dissent += 2
go-to: tertiary

We remind voters of the DVP's industrial ties as a secondary theme without making it the centerpiece.

@secondary_bvp
view-if: (bvp_votes > 0 or bvp_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "BVP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "BVP"; bvp_relation -= 3; z_relation -= 2; workers_bvp *= 0.97
go-to: tertiary

A secondary focus on Bavarian conservatism — limited reach outside the south, but useful.

@secondary_wp
view-if: (wp_votes > 0 or wp_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "WP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "WP"; wp_relation -= 3; old_middle_wp *= 0.99; workers_wp *= 0.98
go-to: tertiary

We note the Economic Party's contradictions in passing — enough to chip at their middle-class base.

@secondary_ddp
view-if: (ddp_votes > 0 or ddp_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "DDP"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "DDP"; ddp_relation -= 4; reformist_dissent += 2; left_dissent -= 2
go-to: tertiary

Secondary criticism of the Democrats registers with the left wing without fully alienating liberals.

@secondary_sapd
view-if: (sapd_votes > 0 or sapd_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "SAPD"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "SAPD"; sapd_relation -= 4; left_dissent += 5; workers_sapd -= 2
go-to: tertiary

We level secondary criticism at the SAPD as a divisive splinter — though the left finds this uncomfortable.

@secondary_csvd
view-if: (csvd_votes > 0 or csvd_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "CSVD"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "CSVD"; csvd_relation -= 3; catholics_csvd *= 0.98; z_relation -= 1
go-to: tertiary

A secondary salvo at the Christian Socials — modest effects, but noted.

@secondary_cnbl
view-if: (cnbl_votes > 0 or cnbl_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "CNBL"
on-arrival: enemy_2 = "CNBL"; cnbl_relation -= 3; rural_cnbl *= 0.98
go-to: tertiary

Secondary fire at the agrarians — limited urban impact but noted in the countryside.

@skip_secondary
on-arrival: enemy_2 = 0
go-to: tertiary

@tertiary

= Our third target

We are already targeting the [+ enemy_1 +] and [? if enemy_2 != 0: the [+ enemy_2 +]. Is there a third party ?][? if enemy_2 = 0: focusing our fire. Is there a secondary party ?] worth a passing criticism?

- @tertiary_kpd: The KPD.
- @tertiary_nsdap: The NSDAP.
- @tertiary_dnvp: The DNVP.
- @tertiary_z: The Zentrum Party.
- @tertiary_dvp: The DVP.
- @tertiary_bvp: The BVP.
- @tertiary_wp: The WP.
- @tertiary_ddp: The DDP.
- @tertiary_sapd: The SAPD.
- @tertiary_csvd: The CSVD.
- @tertiary_cnbl: The CNBL.
- @skip_tertiary: Two targets are sufficient.

@tertiary_kpd
view-if: (kpd_votes > 0 or kpd_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "KPD" and enemy_2 != "KPD" and ideology != "left"
on-arrival: enemy_3 = "KPD"; kpd_relation -= 3; workers_kpd -= 1 if workers_kpd < 25; left_dissent += 2
go-to: enemies_done

@tertiary_nsdap
view-if: (nsdap_votes > 0 or nsdap_r > 0) and enemy_1 != "NSDAP" and enemy_2 != "NSDAP"
